Package it.unipr.sowide.actodes.filtering.constraint

Provides classes and interfaces defining constraints and some useful implementations used for filtering objects.
  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    AggregateConstraint<T>
    The AggregateConstraint interface defines a constraint that can be used for filtering different kinds of objects.
    BinaryConstraint<F,​S>
    The Individual interface defines a constraint that can be used for filtering different kinds of objects.
    Constraint<T>
    The Constraint interface defines a constraint that can be used for filtering different kinds of objects.
    UnaryConstraint<T>
    The Individual interface defines a constraint that can be used for filtering different kinds of objects.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    All<T>
    The All class defines a constraint applied to a group of objects.
    And<T>
    The And class defines a conjunction constraint.
    Contains<T>
    The Contains class defines a constraint applied to a group of objects.
    IsDifferent<T>
    The IsDifferent class defines a diversity comparative constraint.
    IsEqual<T>
    The IsEqual class defines an equality comparative constraint.
    IsHigher<T extends java.lang.Comparable<? super T>>
    The IsHigher class defines a higher comparative constraint.
    IsInstance
    The IsInstance class defines a type constraints.
    IsLower<T extends java.lang.Comparable<? super T>>
    The IsLower class defines lower comparative constraint.
    IsOneOf<T>
    The IsOneOf class defines a membership constraint.
    Matches<T,​P extends Pattern>
    The Matches class defines a pattern constraint.
    Not<T>
    The Not class defines a negation constraint.
    Or<T>
    The Or class defines a disjunction constraint.
    Some<T>
    The Some class defines a constraint applied to a group of objects.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    IsNull
    The IsNull enumeration defines an unbound object field constraint.
